        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 2 at 5:47PM CDT by NWS San Angelo TX</headline>
        <description>At 547 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Doole, moving south at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Melvin, Gouldbusk, Lohn, Rockwood, Pear Valley, Doole, Stacy,
Waldrip, Salt Gap, The Intersection Of Us-
87 And Ranch Road 2134, Fife, Mozelle, and Us-283 Near The Mcculloch-
Coleman County Line.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
